Specs:

0. return string without punctuation
    input: "example: this! string!";
    output: "example this string";

1. explode a string
    input: "here is a string";
    output: array("here", "is", "a", "string");

2. run a loop to identify IF the word is in the exploded string
    input1: "here is a string";
    input2: "here";
    input3: "zebra";

    result2: TRUE;
    result3: FALSE;

3. run a loop to count how many times the word is in the string
    input1: "here is a string";
    input2: "here";
        result: 1;
    input3: "I love love love zebras!";
    input4: "love";
        result: 3;
    input5: "zebra";
        result: 1;
